  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle </p>\n<p>Chop the <strong>spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> finely, discarding the root end<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></p>\n<p>Combine the <strong>beef mince</strong>, <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> and <strong>chopped </strong><strong>spring onion</strong>, then crumble in 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>beef </strong><strong>stock cube</strong> (you will use the rest later!) with a generous amount of <strong>black pepper</strong></p>\n<p>Mix thoroughly with clean hands – this is your <strong>beef mixture</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/602.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/602.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/602.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/602.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/602.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>cheddar cheese</strong> into 4 <span class=\"text-danger\">[8]</span> pieces</p>\n<p>Divide the <strong>beef mixture</strong> in 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span> and shape the mixture into large <strong>meatballs</strong> </p>\n<p>Push two pieces of <strong>cheese</strong> (one on top of the other) into the middle of each meatball, and seal up the outside with mince </p>\n<p>Chill the <strong>meatballs</strong> in the fridge (this ensures they hold their shape when cooking)</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/602.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/602.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/602.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/602.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/602.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>giant</strong> <strong>couscous</strong> to a pot of<strong> boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>\n<p>Cook over a high heat for 8 min, then drain and rinse in a sieve under <strong>cold water</strong></p>\n<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/602.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/602.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/602.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/602.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/602.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid, with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a high heat<strong> </strong></p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>meatballs</strong> and cook for 3 min, moving them around so they cook evenly all over </p>\n<p>Once coloured, transfer them to a plate and set aside</p>\n<p>Keep the pan for the next step</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/602.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/602.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/602.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/602.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/602.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a medium heat, add the <strong>chopped </strong><strong>garlic</strong> and <strong>tomato paste</strong> and cook for 1 min </p>\n<p>Add the <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong>, <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong>, remaining 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>stock cube</strong> and 600ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[1L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>\n<p>Whisk to combine and bring to the boil – this is your <strong>tomato broth </strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
